    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: SHEPPARD M-SERIES - BLEEDING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="x0501514">
        <title>BLEEDING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="drain" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SINGLE GEAR SYSTEM</title>
            <para>Bleeding of the steering gear in a single gear system is only necessary if the gear is mounted in a
                way that will trap air in the sector shaft bore. This procedure should be followed whenever the gear has
                been disassembled, replaced or the steering fluid is replaced.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Park the vehicle on a clean, dry, solid surface, preferably concrete. Set the parking
                    brake and block the wheels. Place the transmission in neutral. Make sure the engine is off.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood or cab.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the fluid level in the reservoir is at the full mark on the dipstick.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the drag link from the pitman arm. Refer to GROUP 05 - STEERING in the CTS-5000
                    Master Service Manual for the correct procedure to remove the drag link for the vehicle being
                    serviced.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start the vehicle and allow the engine to idle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Steer the vehicle from full left to full right several times. The pitman arm must make
                    full travel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the bleeder screw in the plug located on the sector shaft bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501546">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501546" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg05/G0500231.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 46. Locate Bleeder Screw</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use an Allen wrench to open the bleeder screw until non-aerated fluid flows from the
                    bleed screw.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Do not turn the steering wheel with the bleeder open.</para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the bleed screw.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the drag link, and tighten the attaching nut to specifications in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="t0501501">Table 1</hotlnk>following:
                </para>
                <table id="t0501501">
                    <title>Drag Link Nut Torque Chart</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                        <colspec colname="sqcolumn1" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                        <colspec colname="sqcolumn2" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                        <colspec colname="sqcolumn3" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                        <thead valign="top">
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Stud Size</emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Ft-Lbs.</emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Nm</emph>
                                    </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody valign="top">
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>3/4</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>85 to 105</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>116 to 143</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>7/8</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>120 to 160</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <para>163 to 218</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Do not back off the nut when locating the cotter pin hole.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new cotter pin through the ball stud and nut, then lock it in place.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Failure to install and lock a new cotter pin in the ball stud and nut after proper torque
                            could result in an accident, personal injury or death.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If this is a replacement steering gear, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s05015y_X0501506.xml" xrefid="x0501506">SET RELIEF PLUNGERS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the fluid level in the power steering reservoir and fill if necessary.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Shut the vehicle off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the hood or cab.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
